5. PLC: pick up robot:  retrieve warehouse pick data from their Oracle database. Picks are initiated by scanning printed invoices with bar code scanners connected to the PLC controls. This scanned data is retrieved by our software and formatted into a SQL query for the customer database located in Atlanta, Georgia. Location and quantity data from the returned records is then relayed to the PLC controlled robotic pick system. Confirmation of the successful pick is then relayed back to the database.






